HEADWORD: Signaturist
<hw>Sig"na*tur`ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who holds
to the doctrine of signatures impressed upon objects, indicative of
character or qualities.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

